<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-361-966  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 361 966.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Educational Technology  April 1990 v30 n4 p55(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A fully integrated instructional database: promoting studentresearch skills.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Salant, Ami.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Context Information System, a data base devised to encouragethe development of research skills among high school students, isdescribed.andP;  In addition to serving as an instructional databasefor students, the Context system serves as an on-line data base tohelp teachers locate the most update information and materials fortheir courses.andP;  The Context data base can be adapted to theindividual learning styles of students, allowing those withstructured learning styles to work individually while others workin small groups.andP;  The functioning and hardware requirements of theContext Information System are described in detail.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     EducationTechnologyData BasesOn-LineInformation Storage and Retrieval.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   The user interface. (chart)Document descriptions. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>